All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
AddCustomerWindowController
The AddCustomerWindowController controls the interface used add new customers to the database.
Appointment
Contains all data members necessary to retrieve and store appointments in the database
AppointmentQuery
The AppointmentQuery class is an abstract class that holds all methods necessary for performing appointment creation, update, and retrieval to and from the database.
AppointmentsByTypeWindowController
The AppointmentsByTypeWindowController controls the window used to display the Appointments by type report.
Contact
Contains all data members necessary to store Contact information from the database.
ContactQuery
The ContactQuery class is an abstract class containing all methods necessary to access the Contacts table in the database.
Country
Contains all data members necessary to store Country information from the database.
CountryQuery
The CountryQuery class is an abstract class containing all methods necessary to access the Country table in the database.
Customer
Contains all data members necessary to retrieve and store appointments in the database
CustomerAppointmentsWindowController
The CustomerAppointmentsWindowController controls the interface used to display all appointments for a particular customer, as selected in the CustomerInfoWindow.
CustomerInfoWindowController
The CustomerInfoWindowController controls the interface used to display information about all existing customers.
CustomerQuery
The CustomerQuery class is an abstract class containing all methods necessary to access the Customer table in the database.
DivisionQuery
The DivisionQuery class is an abstract class containing all operations needed to access the first_level_division table in the database.
FLDivision
Contains all data members necessary to store First Level Division information from the database.
JDBC
Contains all fields and methods necessary to manage the connection to the database.
LoginController
The LoginController controls the interface used for logging into the application, including name/password validation, access logging, and localization.
Main
Begins the application, loading the login window and initializing the DB connection
MainWindowController
The MainWindowController controls the interface used to display appointments.
MyAppointmentsController
The MyAppointmentsController controls the window used to display the My Appointments report.
NewAppointmentWindowController
The NewAppointmentWindowController controls the interface used to add new appointments to the database
ReportBlock
Class used to store the information needed for the Appointments By Type report.
ReportsQuery
The ReportsQuery class is an abstract class containing all methods needed to generate the My Appointments, Appointments By Type, and Schedule By Contact reports.
ScheduleByContactController
The ScheduleByContactController controls the interface used to display the Schedule By Contact report
StageHandler
Manages stage generation and tracking for the program.
TimeMachine
Contains all methods used to convert and compare dates and times for the program.
UpdateAppointmentWindowController
The UpdateAppointmentWindowController controls the interface used to update existing appointments in the database
UpdateCustomerWindowController
The UpdateCustomerWindowController controls the interface used to update an existing Customer's information in the database
User
Stores information for the current user of the application
UserQuery
The UserQuery class is an abstract class that contains all methods needed to access the Users table in the database.
